ing profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":true,"pe_now":20.9,"pe_percentile":20.0,"median_pe":28.0,"earnings_yield_pct":4.78,"pb":2.19,"ev_ebitda":null,"quality_score":64.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":14.1,"peg":1.49,"cheapness":{"status":"good","read":"P/E at the 20-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 20.9\u00d7 earnings for ~14% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22481.49\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[25.94,25.92,25.91,25.9,25.89,25.88,25.88,25.88,25.88,25.87,25.87,25.87],"latest_pct":25.87,"chg_1y_pp":-0.01},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[41.54,40.97,39.74,37.59,33.16,33.39,32.48,32.65,32.34,29.75,29.36,26.4],"latest_pct":26.4,"chg_1y_pp":-6.25},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2